The paper proposes a deep sequence model with natural explanations derived from case-based reasoning, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses applications in predictive diagnostics for automobiles, ECG, and protein sequence classification, which are areas of research commonly associated with machine learning and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions sentiment analysis on texts, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the results, which is a topic commonly associated with machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SD).
